This Privacy Policy is subject to and governed by our Terms of Service (the “Terms”), available at bundlenews.co. Your use of the Services is subject to your continued compliance with, and agreement to, the Terms. The terms of the foregoing document are hereby incorporated by reference. Any terms capitalized but not herein defined shall be given the meaning ascribed to them by the Terms.
What's in this policy?
This policy tells you:
What information we might collect about you
How we might use that information
When we might use your details to contact you
What information of yours we might share with others
Your choices about the personal information you give us
I. Information We Collect Account Information
When you create an account (“Account”), you will provide information, such as your username, password and email address. You acknowledge that this information may be personal to you and by creating an Account on the Services and providing such information to us, you allow others, including us, to identify you.
If you access the Services using your Google, Facebook, Twitter, or other third party account, we may automatically collect certain information, such as your name, picture, and email address. We will use all information you consent to share through Google, Facebook, Twitter or any other third party platform you use to access the Services, in accordance with the respective policies of these services and your preferences selected through them.
Information we collect through the aforementioned networks also include gender, age, limited location information and demographic information. These information will be used to provide you a better, more personalized experience in the application. It will help us see how different people are using Bundle and check for ways to supply more services for everyone. We may also use some of your personal information to provide recommendations to you on things you’ll like, and to personalize parts of Bunde to your tastes.
We only hold your information for as long as we do the activities we told you about
We think about what type of information it is, the amount collected, how sensitive it might be and any legal requirements
We design our services so that we don’t hold your information any longer than we have to
We generally retain personal data for so long as it may be relevant to the purposes identified herein. To dispose of personal data, we may anonymize it, delete it or take other appropriate steps. Data may persist in copies made for backup and business continuity purposes for additional time.
Our service means that we keep your information inside Bundle unless you ask us or give us your permission to share it, for example:
You ask us to or give us your permission
To provide you with content and services through a partner’s platform
If you have a Bundle account we might use device ID that we hold about you to allow showing you relevant and "targeted advertising" served by other companies' sites, like Facebook, Twitter, Google, MoPub or Firebase. We don’t provide any personal or additional data on Bundle users, or their friends that they do not already have. If you don't want to see our targeted advertising, you can set ad preferences in your social media companies' settings.
We may use your contact information to send you information about our Services or when we believe it is necessary, such as for Account recovery purposes.
Automatically Collected Information
We may also collect, automatically, other non-identifiable information about you when you access the Services, including your Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, browser type and language, Internet Service Provider, information about your Wi-Fi or telecommunications connection (including, without limitation, 2G, 3G, and 4G LTE connections), operating system-provided information or user specific identification information for advertising tracking referring pages, and your usage of near field communication (if any). While this information is non-identifiable, we may aggregate such information based on your geographic location, and transfer such information to third parties in accordance with the terms of this Privacy Policy.
We automatically collect information pertaining to your use of the Services. This information may be used both anonymously and non-anonymously. For example, we automatically collect information pertaining to the articles you read, how far you scroll through various articles, when articles are shared, when you comment on articles, and similar information. This information may be used anonymously to conduct analytics to help us improve the Services, as set forth in Section III, below. This information may also be used non-anonymously to provide you with your own use history, allow you to save articles using your Account, and to otherwise optimize your user experience.
The Application requires permission to read and write upon the storage drive of your device. By using the Services, you agree to provide us with permission for the foregoing.
Location Data
We may collect data about your location while you are using the Services. We may link location data to other information we have collected about you. You may stop sharing your location data by adjusting your mobile device’s location services settings. For instruction on changing the relevant settings, please contact your service provider or device manufacturer.
II. How We Collect Information
In order to enhance your online experience, we use various technologies to collect the information described above, which may include the use of cookies, SDK’s and similar tracking technologies, as provided below:
Cookies
Cookies are small data files stored on your computer’s browser or device that store your preferences, enabling our website to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information including user authentication, user preferences or language preferences. Cookies usually include an anonymous unique identifier and cannot retrieve any other data from your mobile device or pass on computer viruses.
You may be able to disable cookies in your browser or set up your browser to warn you before accepting certain cookies. Please note that if you disable cookies, some features the Services may become difficult or impossible to use.
Software Development Kits (“SDKs”)
We may sometimes use or partner with publishers or app developer platforms that use mobile SDKs, or use an SDK with our Application, to collect information such as mobile identifiers, in order to provide us with information on user devices and how those mobile devices might interact with our Services. We may also use this technology to deliver certain advertisements through the Services based on information associated with your mobile device, as more fully set forth below.
By using the Services, whether as a registered user or otherwise, you acknowledge and agree that you are giving us your consent to track your activities and your use of the Services through the technologies described above, and that we may use such tracking technologies in the emails we send to you.
Advertising platforms, which include Facebook, Twitter, Google, MoPub or Firebase (and whose SDKs are integrated within our Service), may collect information for optimizing advertising campaigns outside of the Service.
If you do not wish to receive personalized advertising that is delivered by third parties outside of the Bundle Service, you may be able to exercise that choice through opt-out programs that are administered by those third parties, including the Network Advertising Initiative (NAI), the Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA). Our Services currently do not respond to “Do Not Track” (DNT) signals and operate as described in this Privacy Policy whether or not a DNT signal is received, as there is no consistent industry standard for compliance.
Why do we use cookies and other tracking?
To do a few different things:
to remember information about you, so you don't have to give it to us again and again.
to keep you signed in, even on different devices
to help us understand how people are using our services, so we can make them better
to deliver advertising to websites outside of the EU
to help us personalize Bundle for you by remembering your preferences, settings and your progress, so you can pause and pick up where you left off reading an article, even on a different device.
A few things on our websites wouldn't work without some cookies. They’re called "strictly necessary cookies". They're always on when you visit us. But we don’t use advertising cookies. Bear in mind there are some other cookies out there from other companies. These "third-party cookies" might track how you use different websites, including ours. For example, you might get a social media company's cookie when you see the option to share something. You can turn them off, but not through us.
