VI. Security of Information
Bundle is committed to protecting the security of your information. As such, we use security controls to protect your information from loss, misuse, unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration and destruction. Further, any information we receive is stored on one or more secure servers, and access to our information systems requires user authentication via password or similar means. Some companies that provide services to us run their services from outside the European Union. We only let that happen if said providers are GDPR compliant in their policies and their levels of security. Keep in mind that when you give us personal information it could be being transferred, stored or processed in a location outside the EU. Despite these precautions, no data security system is impenetrable, and as a result, we cannot ensure the security of information during its transmission between you and us; accordingly, you acknowledge that you do so at your own risk.
If Bundle learns of a security system breach, we may attempt to notify you and provide information on protective measures, if available, through the email address that you have provided to us or by posting a notice on our website.
